{"key":"processedPost-15327893","value":{"id":15327893,"first":15326667,"last":15331962,"when":1320537426,"utime":"11/06/11 01:57 AM","content":"Straw should be compressed during colonization.&nbsp; If using poly tubing ala straw logs, you push really hard when you load it, and the excess moisture drains out the holes in the tubing over a period of a few days after spawning.&nbsp; If using tray culture, you should have a pretty heavy weight on top of the straw bed as it colonizes.&nbsp; This means you should have holes in the bottom of the tray(or laundry basket, etc) for the excess water to drain out.&nbsp; Straw is hollow and you can't just squeeze it with your hands and get enough out.<br />RR","title":"Re: Should I squeeze water out of straw?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}